The paper deals with algorithms and combinatorial complexity bounds for a geometric problem involving point sites in the plane, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The problem involves stable matching, which is a well-studied topic in computer science, and the paper provides a discrete algorithm for constructing the stable-matching Voronoi diagram, which suggests that it could also belong to the algorithms (cs.DS) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also analyzes the combinatorial complexity of the diagram, which suggests that it could belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or game theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
